          "stimulus": "<h5><span style=\"color:#4b0082;\"><span style=\"font-size:1.5em;\"><strong>TASK 5: Quoting, Paraphrasing &amp; Summarising</strong></span></span></h5>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.5em;\"></span><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\"><strong>In task 4 we mentioned the&nbsp;different ways to CITE source material in your work. In this task, read the definition and match it with the type and example that is correct. </strong></span></p>\n",
          "template": "<table class=\"table\">\n\t<thead>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<th class=\"text-center\" scope=\"col\">How is the source used?</th>\n\t\t\t<th class=\"text-center\" scope=\"col\">Definition</th>\n\t\t\t<th class=\"text-center\" scope=\"col\">Example</th>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</thead>\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"text-center\">{{response}}</td>\n\t\t\t<td><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">This involves copying <strong>short sentences</strong> or <strong>sections </strong>(a limit of around 20 words) from a text word-for-word. The words you copy place need to be within ‚Äúquotation marks‚Äù. You also need to give the page number in the citation. </span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"text-center\">{{response}}</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"text-center\">{{response}}</td>\n\t\t\t<td><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">This involves putting a part of a text into your own words by changing the vocabulary, grammar and phrasing of the original text, but <strong>keeping the original meaning</strong> of the text.</span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"text-center\">{{response}}</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"text-center\">{{response}}</td>\n\t\t\t<td><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">This involves giving the main ideas and findings of a text using your own words. This means that you give general overview so it must be <strong>much shorter</strong> than the original text. </span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"text-center\">{{response}}</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n",
